cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.DS

This paper presents a new approach to database schema and instance definition using category theory. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper directly addresses database schema and instance definition. The paper also discusses the use of functors to connect databases and functional programming languages, which could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper's use of category theory suggests it may also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of projections, unions, and joins could place it in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category, and its use of functors could also make it relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
